{"repo": "crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list", "pull_number": 1034, "instance_id": "crweiner__hacktoberfest-swag-list-1034", "issue_numbers": [990, 991], "base_commit": "7f9fdf2a25746dc9aa7e49608b79f6432689c6c6", "patch": "diff --git a/docs/list.md b/docs/list.md\nindex 3ab8acee..5b677efd 100644\n--- a/docs/list.md\n+++ b/docs/list.md\n@@ -53,6 +53,16 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n \n ### C\n \n+#### Cebu Community\n+\n+- **Swag**: Top contributors, best local contributions, and winning teams get special recognition and prizes.  Swag currently unknown.\n+- **Requirements**:\n+    - Form or join teams (up to 4 members) during the kickoff or through community channels.\n+    - The hackathon runs from **October 5 to 26, 2025**\n+    - Contributions to **Cebu-based projects** count double (or carry extra weight)\n+- **How to sign up**: Create an event-specific account via \u201cOneCebby\u201d to stay updated, find teams, and track participation.\n+- **Notes**: Full details on the [Cebu Community blog here](https://hacktoberfest.jscebu.org)\n+\n #### Cloudinary\n \n - **Swag**: The first 30 participants to submit a valid pull request to one of the Cloudinary SDK repos (see below) are rewarded with:\n@@ -69,6 +79,13 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n \n ### D\n \n+#### devICT\n+\n+- **Swag**: Stickers\n+- **Requirements**: Two pull requests to qualifying Wichita projects. Projects include [devICT](https://github.com/devict), [Groover Labs](https://github.com/grooverlabs), [Lake Afton Public Observatory](https://github.com/lake-afton-public-observatory), [MakeICT](https://github.com/makeict), and others.\n+- **How to sign up**: Sign up at their Hacktoberfest webpage below.\n+- **Notes**: Full details on the [devICT website here](https://hacktoberfest.devict.org/)\n+\n #### DocsGPT\n \n - **Swag**: T-shirt\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Add devICT to the Hacktober Swag List for 2025\nA good first issue for people celebrating Hacktoberfest!\n\nPer [here](https://hacktoberfest.devict.org/), devICT is joining in on the Hacktoberfest fun by giving away their own swag for meaningful contributions. \ud83d\ude04\n\nPlease add them to the 2025 list following the formatting in the [CONTRIBUTING.md file.](https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/blob/master/docs/contributing.md)\n\nYou will need to locate the type of swag being offered, their requirements, and a link to their signup form (or some info on how they are tracking contributors).\n\nBe sure to register for Hacktoberfest first by [clicking here.](https://hacktoberfest.com/)\nAdd the Cebu Community to the Hacktober Swag List for 2025\nA good first issue for people celebrating Hacktoberfest!\n\nPer [here](https://hacktoberfest.jscebu.org/), the Cebu Community is joining in on the Hacktoberfest fun by giving away their own swag for meaningful contributions. \ud83d\ude04\n\nPlease add them to the 2025 list following the formatting in the [CONTRIBUTING.md file.](https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/blob/master/docs/contributing.md)\n\nYou will need to locate the type of swag being offered, their requirements, and a link to their signup form (or some info on how they are tracking contributors).\n\nBe sure to register for Hacktoberfest first by [clicking here.](https://hacktoberfest.com/)\n", "hints_text": "please assign this issue to me\nHi @crweiner,\n\nCreated the PR: https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/pull/1021\n\nAs mentioned\n\n\nHi @crweiner,\n\nCreated the PR for this: https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/pull/1021\n\n", "all_hints_text": "please assign this issue to me\nHi @crweiner,\n\nCreated the PR: https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/pull/1021\n\nAs mentioned\n\n\nHi @crweiner,\n\nCreated the PR for this: https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/pull/1021\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/271e2a81ae08fb02ae78ac1ffa9e13dc8688d9d2", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/f4c09269b02f27919215ba9b42b50839b74cf0b2"], "created_at": "2025-10-04T12:58:01Z"}
{"repo": "crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list", "pull_number": 1030, "instance_id": "crweiner__hacktoberfest-swag-list-1030", "issue_numbers": [992, 994, 995, 1007], "base_commit": "3937336ab76b7d8def9f8def519febd084174b1c", "patch": "diff --git a/docs/list.md b/docs/list.md\nindex 69e66815..3ab8acee 100644\n--- a/docs/list.md\n+++ b/docs/list.md\n@@ -114,6 +114,16 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n - **Issues**: Find issues in the [Hyperswitch GitHub Repository](https://github.com/juspay/hyperswitch/issues?q=is%3Aissue%20state%3Aopen%20hacktoberfest%20label%3Ahacktoberfest)\n - **Notes**: Check out the [announcement page](https://hyperswitch.io/hacktoberfest) for more details.\n \n+### I\n+\n+#### Interledger\n+\n+- **Swag**: Unclear, \"Interledger Swag\"\n+- **Requirements**: Unclear, but some kind of \"tiered rewards system\"\n+- **How to sign up**: No known signup link.\n+- **Issues**: [This link shows the included repos and issues](https://github.com/search?q=topic%3Ahacktoberfest+org%3Ainterledger+fork%3Atrue+repo%3Awicg%2Fwebmonetization&type=repositories).\n+- **Notes**: See their [Hacktoberfest page here](https://interledger.org/hacktoberfest).\n+\n ### L\n \n #### Lamatic\n@@ -130,6 +140,16 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n     - [Lamatic Agent Kits Issues](https://github.com/Lamatic/AgentKit/issues)\n - **Notes**: Read the [announcement](https://lamatic.ai/docs/hacktoberfest) for more details.\n \n+#### LambdaTest\n+\n+- **Swag**: Amazon gift cards and LambdaTest Licenses\n+- **Requirements**:\n+    - Have 3+ merged PRs into a [LambdaTest project](https://github.com/LambdaTest/lambdatest-hacktoberfest-2025?tab=readme-ov-file#-projects-you-can-contribute-to).\n+    - 3 Contributions \u2013 Amazon Vouchers (up to $10) and a LambdaTest License (90 days).\n+    - 5 Contributions or More \u2013 Amazon Vouchers (up to $20) and a LambdaTest License (90 days).\n+- **How to sign up**: No known signup link.\n+- **Notes**: Find out more details [in their Hacktoberfest repo](https://github.com/LambdaTest/lambdatest-hacktoberfest-2025).\n+\n ### M\n \n #### **MindsDB**\n@@ -143,6 +163,13 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n - **How to sign up**: No known dedicated signup list.\n - **Notes**: [Check out the MindsDB Hacktoberfest GitHub folder in their repo for full details](https://github.com/mindsdb/mindsdb/tree/main/mindsdb%20hacktoberfest).\n \n+#### Modtoberfest\n+\n+- **Swag**: Sticker pack\n+- **Requirements**: Submit 4 high-quality pull requests to [a participating project.](https://modtoberfest.com/repositories)\n+- **How to sign up**: Join via the [\"Sign Up Here\" button on the home page](https://modtoberfest.com/).\n+- **Notes**: Read all of the [Modtoberfest Rules](https://modtoberfest.com/rules) and the [FAQ](https://modtoberfest.com/faq) to learn more.\n+\n ### Q\n \n #### **QuestDB**\n@@ -155,6 +182,15 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n - **How to sign up**: No known signup method.\n - **Notes**: Read the [contributing](https://github.com/questdb/questdb/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md) guide and check the [QuestDB Hacktoberfest page](https://questdb.io/blog/hacktoberfest-2025-questdb/) for more details.\n \n+### S\n+\n+#### Service Now\n+\n+- **Swag**: ServiceNow merch store codes, and a Community Badge\n+- **Requirements**: Complete all of the 6 PRs for the main Hacktoberfest event, plus [write a comment on this blog post](https://www.servicenow.com/community/developer-advocate-blog/hacktoberfest-2025-building-with-servicenow-giving-with/ba-p/3386849) talking about your contributions and experience\n+- **How to sign up**: You'll need a ServiceNow community account to comment. [Register on the site here](https://account.servicenow.com/sign-up).\n+- **Notes**: Read their [full Hacktoberfest blog post here](https://www.servicenow.com/community/developer-advocate-blog/hacktoberfest-2025-building-with-servicenow-giving-with/ba-p/3386849) and [review the Hacktoberfest repo here](https://github.com/ServiceNowDevProgram/Hacktoberfest).\n+\n ---\n \n *Disclaimer*: This website is a fan and community made creation. It is not affiliated with [Hacktoberfest](https://hacktoberfest.com/) or any company offering swag.\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Add Service Now to the Hacktoberfest Swag List for 2025\nA good first issue for people celebrating Hacktoberfest!\n\nPer [here](https://www.servicenow.com/community/developer-advocate-blog/hacktoberfest-2025-building-with-servicenow-giving-with/ba-p/3386849), Service Now is joining in on the Hacktoberfest fun by giving away their own swag for meaningful contributions. \ud83d\ude04\n\nPlease add them to the 2025 list following the formatting in the [CONTRIBUTING.md file.](https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/blob/master/docs/contributing.md)\n\nYou will need to locate the type of swag being offered, their requirements, and a link to their signup form (or some info on how they are tracking contributors).\n\nBe sure to register for Hacktoberfest first by [clicking here.](https://hacktoberfest.com/)\nAdd Interledger to the Hacktoberfest Swag List for 2025\nA good first issue for people celebrating Hacktoberfest!\n\nPer [here](https://interledger.org/hacktoberfest/), Interledger is joining in on the Hacktoberfest fun by giving away their own swag for meaningful contributions. \ud83d\ude04\n\nPlease add them to the 2025 list following the formatting in the [CONTRIBUTING.md file.](https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/blob/master/docs/contributing.md)\n\nYou will need to locate the type of swag being offered, their requirements, and a link to their signup form (or some info on how they are tracking contributors).\n\nBe sure to register for Hacktoberfest first by [clicking here.](https://hacktoberfest.com/)\nAdd Modtoberefest to the Hacktoberfest Swag List for 2025\nA good first issue for people celebrating Hacktoberfest!\n\nPer [here](https://modtoberfest.com/rules), the Modtoberfest community is joining in on the Hacktoberfest fun by giving away their own swag for meaningful contributions. \n\nPlease add them to the 2025 list following the formatting in the [CONTRIBUTING.md file.](https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/blob/master/docs/contributing.md)\n\nYou will need to locate the type of swag being offered, their requirements, and a link to their signup form (or some info on how they are tracking contributors).\n\nBe sure to register for Hacktoberfest first by [clicking here.](https://hacktoberfest.com/)\nAdd LambdaTest to the Hacktoberfest Swag List for 2025\nA good first issue for people celebrating Hacktoberfest!\n\n[LambdaTest](https://github.com/LambdaTest/lambdatest-hacktoberfest-2025), is joining in on the Hacktoberfest fun. Contribute to LambdaTest projects to win amazon vouchers and LambdaTest licenses.\n\nPlease add them to the 2025 list following the formatting in the [CONTRIBUTING.md file.](https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/blob/master/docs/contributing.md)\n\nYou will need to locate the type of swag being offered, their requirements, and a link to their signup form (or some info on how they are tracking contributors).\n\nBe sure to register for Hacktoberfest first by [clicking here.](https://hacktoberfest.com/)\n\n\n", "hints_text": "please assign this to me\n\nHi @crweiner ,\n\nI would like to work on this issue. Please assign it to me.\n\nThanks!\nHowdy @Dwid4r, I'm not sure why you tagged someone else in your comment, but I assume it was meant for me. \ud83d\ude09\n\nIssues are not assigned, they are first come first served, so feel free to open a PR for me to review. \nHi @crweiner ,\n\nMy apologies for the multiple mentions! I'm still getting familiar with GitHub etiquette. \n\nI'll open the PR now and will avoid unnecessary mentions going forward.\n\nThanks for your patience!\n\nplease assign this to me\n\n\n\n", "all_hints_text": "please assign this to me\n\nHi @crweiner ,\n\nI would like to work on this issue. Please assign it to me.\n\nThanks!\nHowdy @Dwid4r, I'm not sure why you tagged someone else in your comment, but I assume it was meant for me. \ud83d\ude09\n\nIssues are not assigned, they are first come first served, so feel free to open a PR for me to review. \nHi @crweiner ,\n\nMy apologies for the multiple mentions! I'm still getting familiar with GitHub etiquette. \n\nI'll open the PR now and will avoid unnecessary mentions going forward.\n\nThanks for your patience!\n\nplease assign this to me\n\n\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/d8e92312f6db704cb795e07b443a9f43bf85d502"], "created_at": "2025-10-04T10:36:24Z"}
{"repo": "crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list", "pull_number": 1010, "instance_id": "crweiner__hacktoberfest-swag-list-1010", "issue_numbers": [993], "base_commit": "f7b7a66e77485d931af9d4d28b4c62a0c9bef5f5", "patch": "diff --git a/docs/list.md b/docs/list.md\nindex 8e0d838d..f58b7df0 100644\n--- a/docs/list.md\n+++ b/docs/list.md\n@@ -51,6 +51,22 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n - **How to sign up**: Once your PR is merged or Low Code / No Code contribution is published, [submit this form](https://forms.gle/rs5kBkk25ikhgHBg6).\n - **Notes**: Check the [Ballerina Hacktoberfest page](https://ballerina.io/hacktoberfest/) for more details.\n \n+### C\n+\n+#### Cloudinary\n+\n+- **Swag**: The first 30 participants to submit a valid pull request to one of the Cloudinary SDK repos (see below) are rewarded with:\n+    - 1 Cloudinary Hacktoberfest T-shirt (Limited Edition)\n+    - 2 Cloudinary Hacktoberfest Stickers (Limited Edition)\n+    - 3 Cloudinary Stickers\n+    - 1 Cloudinary Unicorn\n+- **Requirements**:\n+    - Open an Issue on the [Official SDK](https://cloudinary.com/blog/hacktoberfest-2025#official_sdks) or [Community SDK](https://cloudinary.com/blog/hacktoberfest-2025#community_sdks) repos\n+    - Make a valid PR to fix the issue\n+    - Spam PRs or small changes do not count towards swag.\n+- **How to sign up**: Once your contribution is accepted and merged, they'll provide you with an address form.\n+- **Notes**: Full details on the [Cloudinary blog here](https://cloudinary.com/blog/hacktoberfest-2025)\n+\n ### G\n \n #### **goose**\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Add Cloudinary to the Hacktoberfest Swag List for 2025\nA good first issue for people celebrating Hacktoberfest!\n\nPer [here](https://cloudinary.com/blog/hacktoberfest-2025), Cloudinary is joining in on the Hacktoberfest fun by giving away their own swag for meaningful contributions. \ud83d\ude04\n\nPlease add them to the 2025 list following the formatting in the [CONTRIBUTING.md file.](https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/blob/master/docs/contributing.md)\n\nYou will need to locate the type of swag being offered, their requirements, and a link to their signup form (or some info on how they are tracking contributors).\n\nBe sure to register for Hacktoberfest first by [clicking here.](https://hacktoberfest.com/)\n", "hints_text": "Hi @crweiner , would you be able to assign me to this Issue?\nThanks in advance!\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Hi @crweiner , would you be able to assign me to this Issue?\nThanks in advance!\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/d4db6838ff9e4766423130093373235d9136bf9d", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/601e4c9b296060f277f0c9984ad8257ad3a11269", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/b52b453f1e0804be5cc1c488327f4cd98ea43ebc", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/31a80e17aa50df9ff9a50f265a927bb05945fa76"], "created_at": "2025-10-01T23:04:00Z"}
{"repo": "crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list", "pull_number": 1005, "instance_id": "crweiner__hacktoberfest-swag-list-1005", "issue_numbers": [997], "base_commit": "af3fe06c5471638f8853b87f15f27b7086c6c185", "patch": "diff --git a/docs/list.md b/docs/list.md\nindex 77cd882a..bcc1531f 100644\n--- a/docs/list.md\n+++ b/docs/list.md\n@@ -30,8 +30,6 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n \n ## A to Z Order of Companies\n \n-### A\n-\n ### B\n \n #### **Ballerina**\n@@ -41,6 +39,18 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n - **How to sign up**: Once your PR is merged or Low Code / No Code contribution is published, [submit this form](https://forms.gle/rs5kBkk25ikhgHBg6).\n - **Notes**: Check the [Ballerina Hacktoberfest page](https://ballerina.io/hacktoberfest/) for more details.\n \n+### Q\n+\n+#### **QuestDB**\n+\n+- **Swag**: T-shirt and stickers.\n+- **Requirements**:  Contribute to open issues at one of the three participating repositories:\n+    - [QuestDB Core](https://github.com/questdb/questdb/issues?q=is%3Aissue+is%3Aopen+label%3Ahacktoberfest)\n+    - [Web Console](https://github.com/questdb/ui/issues?q=is%3Aissue+is%3Aopen+label%3Ahacktoberfest)\n+    - [Documentation](https://github.com/questdb/documentation/issues?q=is%3Aissue+is%3Aopen+label%3Ahacktoberfest)\n+- **How to sign up**: No known signup method.\n+- **Notes**: Read the [contributing](https://github.com/questdb/questdb/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md) guide and check the [QuestDB Hacktoberfest page](https://questdb.io/blog/hacktoberfest-2025-questdb/) for more details.\n+\n *To be filled in as Hacktoberfest 2025 progresses!*\n \n ---\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Add QuestDB to the Hacktoberfest Swag List for 2025\nA good first issue for people celebrating Hacktoberfest!\n\nPer [here](https://questdb.com/blog/hacktoberfest-2025-questdb/), QuestDB is joining in on the Hacktoberfest fun by giving away their own swag for meaningful contributions.\n\nPlease add them to the 2025 list following the formatting in the [CONTRIBUTING.md file.](https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/blob/master/docs/contributing.md)\n\nYou will need to locate the type of swag being offered, their requirements, and a link to their signup form (or some info on how they are tracking contributors).\n\nBe sure to register for Hacktoberfest first by [clicking here.](https://hacktoberfest.com/)\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/80385a8ba38b0b20d33d44ebe8aa1c7fa436c163", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/54fc217fd4a012dd6dc4e357c502c2290ee9659b", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/7fb840997e68ef84f860852a0c4eef097496d970", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/372461c73626483c6af44b69f00b22377b50e31a", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/76d4c8c5df8e1a1132d691f8651228d5c15c1ccc", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/4cffa244a6f60da24772fd0f35b5cb3fbe8f819a", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/93c81da023ff99108bd5a8e80f707022cfe997f2", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/e1739101e65e6d5ffe2e7939c9dd013095fecfeb"], "created_at": "2025-10-01T04:22:18Z"}
{"repo": "crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list", "pull_number": 1026, "instance_id": "crweiner__hacktoberfest-swag-list-1026", "issue_numbers": [998], "base_commit": "7f9fdf2a25746dc9aa7e49608b79f6432689c6c6", "patch": "diff --git a/docs/list.md b/docs/list.md\nindex 3ab8acee..d35d9479 100644\n--- a/docs/list.md\n+++ b/docs/list.md\n@@ -79,6 +79,17 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n - **Issues**: [DocsGPT/issues](https://github.com/arc53/DocsGPT/issues)\n - **Notes**: Check the [announcement](https://github.com/arc53/DocsGPT/blob/main/HACKTOBERFEST.md) for more details.\n \n+#### Dodo Payments\n+\n+- **Swag**: Swag pack (T-shirt, cap, and stickers).\n+- **Requirements**:\n+    - Claim the issue and outline your approach.\n+    - Work on the issue and implement code or docs and add tests.\n+    - Make meaningful PRs which include everything that is needed.\n+- **How to sign up**: Sign up here [Dodo Payments Sign up](https://app.dodopayments.com/signup).\n+- **Issues**: Check open issues or open one in the participating repositories.\n+- **Notes**: Read the rules and find all the participating repositories on the [announcement page](https://dodopayments.com/blogs/hacktoberfest-2025-dodo-payments).\n+\n #### .NET Foundation (dotnet)\n \n - **Swag**: Digital certificate for Hacktoberfest.\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Add Dodo Payments to the Hacktoberfest Swag List for 2025\nA good first issue for people celebrating Hacktoberfest!\n\nPer [here](https://dodopayments.com/blogs/hacktoberfest-2025-dodo-payments), Dodo Payments is joining in on the Hacktoberfest fun by giving away their own swag for meaningful contributions. \n\nPlease add them to the 2025 list following the formatting in the [CONTRIBUTING.md file.](https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/blob/master/docs/contributing.md)\n\nYou will need to locate the type of swag being offered, their requirements, and a link to their signup form (or some info on how they are tracking contributors).\n\nBe sure to register for Hacktoberfest first by [clicking here.](https://hacktoberfest.com/)\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "please assign this issue to me\n\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/c94e6a78e56072a35591af36b8e2f7948aa945fc", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/2e7a1f025f13c4b5e856399dfed9383d3a6dad0a", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/2beb8256c1f08483b0c55611962b0053bd6875df", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/1fdad2f776ca65162cc7de7f942107755ca58ef8", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/805f40710cf59afab61c23f9c55776d4cdef402c", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/4dd6914b2647a839f01d01a068cb1856b60e9141"], "created_at": "2025-10-02T21:09:20Z"}
{"repo": "crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list", "pull_number": 1006, "instance_id": "crweiner__hacktoberfest-swag-list-1006", "issue_numbers": [1002], "base_commit": "b6d9415e5ce9cb79ac354a02c65b3c2e1aeabf64", "patch": "diff --git a/docs/list.md b/docs/list.md\nindex 465b9a30..9a0514aa 100644\n--- a/docs/list.md\n+++ b/docs/list.md\n@@ -32,6 +32,16 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n \n ### A\n \n+#### Appwrite\n+\n+- **Swag**: Appwrite Swag kit (Customized hoodie, T-shirt, Mouse pad, and Stickers)\n+- **Requirements**:\n+  - Build and deploy a project from scratch using Appwrite Cloud\n+  - Add a project submission to the [appwrite-community/hf2025-hackathon-submissions](https://github.com/appwrite-community/hf2025-hackathon-submissions) repo.\n+  - Submit PR details on the [hackathon portal (when logged in).](https://hacktoberfest.appwrite.network/hacker/submit)\n+- **How to sign up**: [Sign up](https://hacktoberfest.appwrite.network/) for the Hackathon.\n+- **Notes**: Check out the rules and FAQ at the [Appwrite Hacktoberfest Hackathon page](https://hacktoberfest.appwrite.network/#rules), and [a video for how to join the hackathon](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fyQOT93O8Do).\n+\n *To be filled in as Hacktoberfest 2025 progresses!*\n \n ---\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Add Appwrite to the Hacktoberfest Swag List for 2025\nA good first issue for people celebrating Hacktoberfest!\n\n[Appwrite](https://hacktoberfest.appwrite.network/), is joining in on the Hacktoberfest fun with a Hackathon.\nBuild and deploy apps using Appwrite cloud and stand a chance to win Appwrite Swag kit.\n\nPlease add them to the 2025 list following the formatting in the [CONTRIBUTING.md file.](https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/blob/master/docs/contributing.md?rgh-link-date=2025-09-30T03%3A31%3A08.000Z)\n\nYou will need to locate the type of swag being offered, their requirements, and a link to their signup form (or some info on how they are tracking contributors).\n\nBe sure to register for Hacktoberfest first by [clicking here.](https://hacktoberfest.com/)\n\n\n", "hints_text": "hi, i would like to contribute, can u pls assign me this ?\n\n", "all_hints_text": "hi, i would like to contribute, can u pls assign me this ?\nHi @crweiner I have made a PR #1006 for this issue.\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/d200f76e8cebae733cdbea27f0f52b25f9714f41", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/02107dc4f3143d0607c2e13b92aabb981d7ab484", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/cad9ad6b1b930a6d96ccb71225b75326e6a4e237"], "created_at": "2025-10-01T07:00:58Z"}
{"repo": "crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list", "pull_number": 1009, "instance_id": "crweiner__hacktoberfest-swag-list-1009", "issue_numbers": [1004], "base_commit": "6b469bc0a89efc180131471d932bf0227422eea2", "patch": "diff --git a/docs/list.md b/docs/list.md\nindex 220c5fca..8e0d838d 100644\n--- a/docs/list.md\n+++ b/docs/list.md\n@@ -51,6 +51,19 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n - **How to sign up**: Once your PR is merged or Low Code / No Code contribution is published, [submit this form](https://forms.gle/rs5kBkk25ikhgHBg6).\n - **Notes**: Check the [Ballerina Hacktoberfest page](https://ballerina.io/hacktoberfest/) for more details.\n \n+### G\n+\n+#### **goose**\n+\n+- **Swag**: Gift cards to the goose swag shop and LLM credits.\n+- **Requirements**: PRs must be merged with the `hacktoberfest-accepted` label to `hacktoberfest`-labeled issues in the [goose repository](https://github.com/block/goose). Grab issues by commenting \".take\". Points are awarded based on contribution size (small: 5 points, medium: 10 points, large: 15 points). Top 20 contributors win prizes.\n+    - Top 1-5 Contributors: $100 gift card to goose swag shop + $100 LLM credits\n+    - Top 6-10 Contributors: $50 gift card to goose swag shop + $50 LLM credits\n+    - Top 11-20 Contributors: $25 LLM credits\n+- **How to sign up**: No known signup link, but it seems to be automated. [Check the Leaderboard here](https://github.com/block/goose/issues/4775).\n+- **Issues**: Find issues in the [goose Hacktoberfest 2025 Project Hub](https://github.com/block/goose/issues/4705).\n+- **Notes**: [Check out the goose Hacktoberfest 2025 blog post for full details](https://block.github.io/goose/blog/2025/09/26/hacktoberfest-2025/) and the [pinned Hacktoberfest issue](https://github.com/block/goose/issues/4705).\n+\n ### Q\n \n #### **QuestDB**\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Add goose to the Hacktoberfest Swag List for 2025\nA good first issue for people celebrating Hacktoberfest!\n\n[goose](https://block.github.io/goose/blog/2025/09/26/hacktoberfest-2025), is joining in on the Hacktoberfest fun. Build features, fix bugs, fix documentation or contribute to any open issue to gain points to stand a chance to win swag and LLM credits.\n\nPlease add them to the 2025 list following the formatting in the [CONTRIBUTING.md file.](https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/blob/master/docs/contributing.md?rgh-link-date=2025-09-30T03%3A31%3A08.000Z)\n\nYou will need to locate the type of swag being offered, their requirements, and a link to their signup form (or some info on how they are tracking contributors).\n\nBe sure to register for Hacktoberfest first by [clicking here.](https://hacktoberfest.com/)\n\n\n", "hints_text": "@vimode Can i take up this issue?\n\ud83d\udc4b  @nu11Orbit \nIssues are not assigned here. The first valid PR gets merged. So feel free to open a new PR. \n\n", "all_hints_text": "@vimode Can i take up this issue?\n\ud83d\udc4b  @nu11Orbit \nIssues are not assigned here. The first valid PR gets merged. So feel free to open a new PR. \n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/d9db91da98a00280919148aed32b6fcc16657678", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/442efc90e9e84feb7df3fafb4230b116556a2993", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/37c63e430fe8a518d80948f1608fe9f83225627a"], "created_at": "2025-10-01T22:36:00Z"}
{"repo": "crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list", "pull_number": 1027, "instance_id": "crweiner__hacktoberfest-swag-list-1027", "issue_numbers": [1008], "base_commit": "5be3b436a107f114193a179ea976a44872da96a2", "patch": "diff --git a/docs/list.md b/docs/list.md\nindex e294216c..69e66815 100644\n--- a/docs/list.md\n+++ b/docs/list.md\n@@ -101,6 +101,19 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n - **Issues**: Find issues in the [goose Hacktoberfest 2025 Project Hub](https://github.com/block/goose/issues/4705).\n - **Notes**: [Check out the goose Hacktoberfest 2025 blog post for full details](https://block.github.io/goose/blog/2025/09/26/hacktoberfest-2025/) and the [pinned Hacktoberfest issue](https://github.com/block/goose/issues/4705).\n \n+### H\n+\n+#### Hyperswitch\n+\n+- **Swag**: T-shirt and Hoodie\n+- **Requirements**:\n+    - Contribute to open issues with good first issue and help wanted tags.\n+    - 1 merged PR: T-shirt\n+    - 3+ merged PRs: T-shirt and Hoodie\n+- **How to sign up**: No known signup method.\n+- **Issues**: Find issues in the [Hyperswitch GitHub Repository](https://github.com/juspay/hyperswitch/issues?q=is%3Aissue%20state%3Aopen%20hacktoberfest%20label%3Ahacktoberfest)\n+- **Notes**: Check out the [announcement page](https://hyperswitch.io/hacktoberfest) for more details.\n+\n ### L\n \n #### Lamatic\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Add Hyperswitch to the Hacktoberfest Swag List for 2025\nA good first issue for people celebrating Hacktoberfest!\n\n[Hyperswitch](https://github.com/juspay/hyperswitch/discussions/9473), is joining in on the Hacktoberfest fun. Contribute to issues at Hyperswitch to win T-shirt and other swag.\n\nPlease add them to the 2025 list following the formatting in the [CONTRIBUTING.md file.](https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/blob/master/docs/contributing.md)\n\nYou will need to locate the type of swag being offered, their requirements, and a link to their signup form (or some info on how they are tracking contributors).\n\nBe sure to register for Hacktoberfest first by [clicking here.](https://hacktoberfest.com/)\n\n\n", "hints_text": "Announcement post - https://hyperswitch.io/hacktoberfest\nHi! I\u2019d love to give this a try as part of Hacktoberfest. Can you assign this to me?\n@Mrdanish24 \ud83d\udc4b \n Issues are not assigned here. The first valid PR gets merged. So feel free to open a new PR.\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Announcement post - https://hyperswitch.io/hacktoberfest\nHi! I\u2019d love to give this a try as part of Hacktoberfest. Can you assign this to me?\n@Mrdanish24 \ud83d\udc4b \n Issues are not assigned here. The first valid PR gets merged. So feel free to open a new PR.\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/f9101728a260739884f1cdcf3927568f342326fd", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/52fd112b7000bb3a17e9391791fffb2f6198abfd", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/e11f5153f65ad1f836baffc8483711bc7a0b43dc", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/7a608413ecbb6ddb93f9983b4d137f45c301aa8a"], "created_at": "2025-10-03T07:45:45Z"}
{"repo": "crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list", "pull_number": 1012, "instance_id": "crweiner__hacktoberfest-swag-list-1012", "issue_numbers": [1011], "base_commit": "b6d9415e5ce9cb79ac354a02c65b3c2e1aeabf64", "patch": "diff --git a/docs/list.md b/docs/list.md\nindex 465b9a30..ec6a6e12 100644\n--- a/docs/list.md\n+++ b/docs/list.md\n@@ -34,6 +34,19 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n \n *To be filled in as Hacktoberfest 2025 progresses!*\n \n+### M\n+\n+#### **MindsDB**\n+\n+- **Swag**: Github Sponsorship, MindsDB T-shirt, MacBook Pro\n+- **Requirements**:\n+    - Build an application with MindsDB Knowledge Bases + MindsDB, and write a blog post explaining how it works. Share it on Linkedin, and X/Twitter with a post mentioning @MindsDB.\n+    - Write a pull request with your use-case implementation in the use-cases folder (create a folder for your use case with a descriptive name)\n+    - Top 3 PRs, top 3 social media posts and 3 best blog posts will receive cash prizes as GitHub sponsorships and T-Shirt.\n+    - Every winner will get 1 entry into the Apple MacBook Pro prize draw.\n+- **How to sign up**: No known dedicated signup list.\n+- **Notes**: [Check out the MindsDB Hacktoberfest GitHub folder in their repo for full details](https://github.com/mindsdb/mindsdb/tree/main/mindsdb%20hacktoberfest).\n+\n ---\n \n *Disclaimer*: This website is a fan and community made creation. It is not affiliated with [Hacktoberfest](https://hacktoberfest.com/) or any company offering swag.\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Add mindsdb to the Hacktoberfest Swag List for 2025\nA good first issue for people celebrating Hacktoberfest!\n\n[MindsDB](https://mindsdb.com/), is joining in on the Hacktoberfest fun with a Hackathon.\nBuild apps using MindsDB knowledge base and stand a chance to win Macbook Pro.\n\nPlease add them to the 2025 list following the formatting in the [CONTRIBUTING.md file.](https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/blob/master/docs/contributing.md?rgh-link-date=2025-09-30T03%3A31%3A08.000Z)\n\nYou will need to locate the type of swag being offered, their requirements, and a link to their signup form (or some info on how they are tracking contributors).\n\nBe sure to register for Hacktoberfest first by [clicking here.](https://hacktoberfest.com/)\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Hi @crweiner PR for this issue - #1012 \nI'd like to work on this issue for Hacktoberfest. Please assign it to me.\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/ab6290bac78d06dd21f00e757f69e32f6c24cf0b", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/f03e22ba224b0bd1d2825b377337a2bd00c5ba77", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/091bfe152a4dde674d9ca86bbb05f217bbfcd9ca", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/a0abeef5d2f2f5df8a7ab1cc34b2fad03bb4eee3", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/c15b2fc479e99ff09ac2ae51da687d563d2629ba"], "created_at": "2025-10-02T00:50:25Z"}
{"repo": "crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list", "pull_number": 1017, "instance_id": "crweiner__hacktoberfest-swag-list-1017", "issue_numbers": [1013], "base_commit": "5e1e3de5998d7ef1b8fd93b14a7a8d90279a9756", "patch": "diff --git a/docs/list.md b/docs/list.md\nindex f58b7df0..c3340616 100644\n--- a/docs/list.md\n+++ b/docs/list.md\n@@ -80,6 +80,22 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n - **Issues**: Find issues in the [goose Hacktoberfest 2025 Project Hub](https://github.com/block/goose/issues/4705).\n - **Notes**: [Check out the goose Hacktoberfest 2025 blog post for full details](https://block.github.io/goose/blog/2025/09/26/hacktoberfest-2025/) and the [pinned Hacktoberfest issue](https://github.com/block/goose/issues/4705).\n \n+### L\n+\n+#### Lamatic\n+\n+- **Swag**: T-shirt, stickers, exclusive Lamatic swag\n+- **Requirements**:\n+    - Make 4 valid PRs to any of the three repositories.\n+    - PRs must be valid and follow project guidelines.\n+    - Add `hacktoberfest` tag to PR title or description.\n+- **How to sign up**: No known signup link.\n+- **Issues**:\n+    - [Lamatic SDK Issues](https://github.com/Lamatic/lamatic-sdk/issues)\n+    - [Lamatic Docs Issues](https://github.com/Lamatic/Lamatic-Docs/issues)\n+    - [Lamatic Agent Kits Issues](https://github.com/Lamatic/AgentKit/issues)\n+- **Notes**: Read the [announcement](https://lamatic.ai/docs/hacktoberfest) for more details.\n+\n ### Q\n \n #### **QuestDB**\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Add Lamatic to the Hacktoberfest Swag List for 2025\nA good first issue for people celebrating Hacktoberfest!\n\n[Lamatic](https://lamatic.ai/docs/hacktoberfest), is joining in on the Hacktoberfest fun. Contribute to issues at Lamatic to win swag.\n\nPlease add them to the 2025 list following the formatting in the [CONTRIBUTING.md file.](https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/blob/master/docs/contributing.md)\n\nYou will need to locate the type of swag being offered, their requirements, and a link to their signup form (or some info on how they are tracking contributors).\n\nBe sure to register for Hacktoberfest first by [clicking here.](https://hacktoberfest.com/)\n\n\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/e18d011576056b42023dfd81aee67593cd2e435d", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/69cf312c06527bfe5cdcdb81cff8d1e4bdd2f4fb", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/0fbf32754037b505255928a582a97f51f638aa5c"], "created_at": "2025-10-02T04:53:20Z"}
{"repo": "crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list", "pull_number": 1041, "instance_id": "crweiner__hacktoberfest-swag-list-1041", "issue_numbers": [1014], "base_commit": "7f9fdf2a25746dc9aa7e49608b79f6432689c6c6", "patch": "diff --git a/docs/list.md b/docs/list.md\nindex 3ab8acee..1a346119 100644\n--- a/docs/list.md\n+++ b/docs/list.md\n@@ -67,6 +67,18 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n - **How to sign up**: Once your contribution is accepted and merged, they'll provide you with an address form.\n - **Notes**: Full details on the [Cloudinary blog here](https://cloudinary.com/blog/hacktoberfest-2025)\n \n+#### **CopilotKit**\n+\n+- **Swag**: CopilotKit swag\n+- **Requirements**:\n+    - Project Setup and Guidelines: Follow the instructions in [CONTRIBUTING.md](https://github.com/CopilotKit/CopilotKit/blob/main/community/content/CONTRIBUTING.md).\n+    - Choose an Issue tagged `hacktoberfest`, see the link below.\n+    - Submit Your Demo: Build and submit your demo as per **CONTRIBUTING.md**.\n+    - Share Your Project: Post on X/Twitter tagging `@Copilotkit` and using **#CopilotKitHacktoberfest**; top-liked projects win,\n+- **How to sign up**: No signup needed.\n+- **Issues**: See the list of open `hacktoberfest` [issues here](https://github.com/CopilotKit/CopilotKit/issues?q=sort:updated-desc+is:issue+is:open+label:hacktoberfest).\n+- **Notes**: Check out the [announcement post](https://github.com/CopilotKit/CopilotKit/tree/main/community/content) for more details.\n+\n ### D\n \n #### DocsGPT\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Add CopilotKit to the Hacktoberfest Swag List for 2025\nA good first issue for people celebrating Hacktoberfest!\n\n[CopilotKit](https://github.com/CopilotKit/CopilotKit/blob/main/community/content/README.md), is joining in on the Hacktoberfest fun. Build and submit a project to win a certificate and a chance to win some swag.\n\nPlease add them to the 2025 list following the formatting in the [CONTRIBUTING.md file.](https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/blob/master/docs/contributing.md)\n\nYou will need to locate the type of swag being offered, their requirements, and a link to their signup form (or some info on how they are tracking contributors).\n\nBe sure to register for Hacktoberfest first by [clicking here.](https://hacktoberfest.com/)\n\n\n", "hints_text": "I'd like to work on this issue for Hacktoberfest. Please assign it to me.\n\n\n", "all_hints_text": "I'd like to work on this issue for Hacktoberfest. Please assign it to me.\n\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/e16289f1de73e4dae1bdc07c235a5ec091c69177", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/acd0d1323a41f5211d8873a364d64ce1bcb83fc3", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/df4a9c24e873ced8428410168fe2ae7c62be6178"], "created_at": "2025-10-05T19:11:17Z"}
{"repo": "crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list", "pull_number": 1075, "instance_id": "crweiner__hacktoberfest-swag-list-1075", "issue_numbers": [1015], "base_commit": "d9f65c568c9825518f8bc7d076b4a5f89664635f", "patch": "diff --git a/docs/list.md b/docs/list.md\nindex bc1995d3..13a5fcc1 100644\n--- a/docs/list.md\n+++ b/docs/list.md\n@@ -153,8 +153,38 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n - **How to sign up**: When your PR is accepted or merged, fill [this claim form](https://forms.cloud.microsoft/r/vS3YhKMEvL?utm_source=chatgpt.com) which will open during Oct 27-31 (UTC).\n - **Notes**: Full details on the [.NET Foundation blog here](https://dotnetfoundation.org/community/hacktoberfest).\n \n+### F\n+\n+#### Flexprice\n+\n+- **Swag**: Flexprice Hacktoberfest swag pack (stickers, T-shirt, and tote bag) + social media shoutouts for top contributors.\n+- **Requirements**:\n+    - Join the [Flexprice Slack community](https://join.slack.com/t/flexpricecommunity/shared_invite/zt-39uat51l0-n8JmSikHZP~bHJNXladeaQ).\n+    - Contribute between **Oct 1\u201331, 2025** to any of the following repositories:\n+        - [Flexprice](https://github.com/flexprice/flexprice)\n+        - [Flexprice Dashboard](https://github.com/flexprice/flexprice-front/issues)\n+        - [Flexprice Docs](https://github.com/flexprice/flexprice-docs/issues)\n+        - [Flexprice SDKs (TS/Python/Go)](https://github.com/flexprice/javascript-sdk/issues)\n+    - Pick an issue labelled `hacktoberfest`, `good first issue`, `help wanted`, `bug`, `enhancement`, or `documentation`.\n+    - Comment \u201cI\u2019m on it\u201d, open a PR that passes checks, and follows the contribution template.\n+- **How to sign up**: No separate signup form \u2014 contributions are tracked automatically via merged PRs and Slack participation.\n+- **Issues**: [Flexprice Hacktoberfest issues](https://github.com/flexprice/flexprice/issues?q=is%3Aissue+label%3Ahacktoberfest)\n+- **Notes**: [Official announcement on X (Twitter)](https://twitter-thread.com/t/1974412729990701385).\n+\n ### G\n \n+#### **GibsonAI**\n+\n+- **Swag**: T-shirt, stickers and a surprise swag pack.\n+- **Requirements**:\n+    - Contribute to GibsonAI/memori, be eligible to win awards based on contribution level.\n+    - Level 1 - Fix issues or improve documentation to win stickers.\n+    - Level 2 - For feature enhancement or new integration win a T-shirt.\n+    - Level 3 - Add major feature to win a swag pack with surprise inside.\n+- **How to sign up**: No known signup link.\n+- **Issues**: [All open issues at GibsonAI/memori](https://github.com/GibsonAI/memori/issues?q=sort%3Aupdated-desc+is%3Aissue+is%3Aopen).\n+- **Notes**: Check the [GibsonAI/memori repository](https://github.com/GibsonAI/memori/issues/127) for more details.\n+\n #### **Globo**\n \n - **Swag**: T-shirt.\n@@ -168,7 +198,7 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n #### **goose**\n \n - **Swag**: Gift cards to the goose swag shop and LLM credits.\n-- **Requirements**: PRs must be merged with the `hacktoberfest-accepted` label to `hacktoberfest`-labeled issues in the [goose repository](https://github.com/block/goose). Grab issues by commenting \".take\". Points are awarded based on contribution size (small: 5 points, medium: 10 points, large: 15 points). Top 20 contributors win prizes.\n+- **Requirements**: PRs must be merged with the `hacktoberfest-accepted` label to `hacktoberfest` labelled issues in the [goose repository](https://github.com/block/goose). Grab issues by commenting \".take\". Points are awarded based on contribution size (small: 5 points, medium: 10 points, large: 15 points). Top 20 contributors win prizes.\n     - Top 1-5 Contributors: $100 gift card to goose swag shop + $100 LLM credits\n     - Top 6-10 Contributors: $50 gift card to goose swag shop + $50 LLM credits\n     - Top 11-20 Contributors: $25 LLM credits\n@@ -306,6 +336,18 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n - **How to sign up**: Register for [Global Hack Week](https://ghw.mlh.io) and complete the full check-in steps listed above.\n - **Notes**: Please see [more swag details here](https://ghw.mlh.io/swag).\n \n+### O\n+\n+#### **Olake**\n+\n+- **Swag**: Jacket, diaries, pens and stickers.\n+- **Requirements**:  Contribute to open issues at one of the two participating Olake repositories.\n+- **How to sign up**: No known signup method.\n+- **Issues**:\n+      - [Olake UI](https://github.com/datazip-inc/olake-ui/issues)\n+      - [Olake Core](https://github.com/datazip-inc/olake/issues)\n+- **Notes**: For more information check out [this post on X](https://x.com/cappybaradeploy/status/1973027154041729331).\n+\n ### Q\n \n #### **QuestDB**\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Add Olake to the Hacktoberfest Swag List for 2025\nA good first issue for people celebrating Hacktoberfest!\n\n[Olake](https://x.com/cappybaradeploy/status/1973027154041729331), is joining in on the Hacktoberfest fun. Make meaningful contributions to open issues, get your PR merged to get swag like a jacket, pen, stickers, diaries\n\nPlease add them to the 2025 list following the formatting in the [CONTRIBUTING.md file.](https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/blob/master/docs/contributing.md)\n\nYou will need to locate the type of swag being offered, their requirements, and a link to their signup form (or some info on how they are tracking contributors).\n\nBe sure to register for Hacktoberfest first by [clicking here.](https://hacktoberfest.com/)\n\nThe tweet\n\n> The only way to get off campus opportunites is contribution to open source and this might be your chance to build world's fastest data replication tool .\n> \n> [@_olake](https://x.com/_olake)\n>   just went orange this halloween.\n> Why? \n> [@hacktoberfest](https://x.com/hacktoberfest)\n>  !!\n> I\u2019ve always supported open source and liked my github - greeener the better .\n> \n> Now we\u2019re welcoming pull requests and submissions for two of our core repositories- UI and Core. This is your chance to help build the world\u2019s fastest data application tool.\n> \n> Step two is simple: \n> get those PRs merged. Join our Slack. Contributors are already there, discussing ideas and helping each other. \n> No pressure, no judging by the conversation count :)\n> And yes, there are perks alongwith hacktoberfest goodies we have..\n> \n> The jacket I\u2019m wearing?\n> You can get it. \n> Plus diaries, pens, stickers.\n> \n> If an opening comes up, contributors will always get priority.\n> Check out the repos. \n> Start with the good first issues they\u2019re beginner-friendly. \n> If you\u2019re more technical, explore deeper.\n> We support TypeScript, JavaScript, and Golang.\n> \n> Repository links are in the comments. See you on GitHub and Slack.\n> \n\n> GitHub (core): [https://github.com/datazip-inc/olake/issues\n>  \n>  GitHub (UI): [https://github.com/datazip-inc/olake-ui/issues\n> \n> Slack- https://olake.io/slack/\n> \n> Best of luck for this month of open source, can\u2019t wait to build with you!\n> \n", "hints_text": "Hi @vimode , I\u2019d like to work on this issue.\nCould you please assign it to me?\n\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Hi @vimode , I\u2019d like to work on this issue.\nCould you please assign it to me?\n\nHi! \ud83d\udc4b I would like to work on this issue. Please assign it to me.\n\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/90545eb0f343906eeeaef3cfc9a6f39b1b4c631b", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/c4e589f9257e2d55b5a778b911210b453c809a03", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/dc65a3ed5e4aedf6f4e5ef93aa8028a809cc37fa", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/0ff9ca5ef58af212cdd01bef4b3d0154284c5f79", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/859a73b52a4dd5d76b096911922f374c10829132", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/52d1e1079a02b181aaead462ee6a517c589a42ee", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/6d04d92d280b3b3b19c402b05515423e298da91a"], "created_at": "2025-10-25T12:36:49Z"}
{"repo": "crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list", "pull_number": 1050, "instance_id": "crweiner__hacktoberfest-swag-list-1050", "issue_numbers": [1047], "base_commit": "db9214f72ad72fe62d63b35673b300ecba0006f5", "patch": "diff --git a/docs/list.md b/docs/list.md\nindex 9d23a9cb..6522522a 100644\n--- a/docs/list.md\n+++ b/docs/list.md\n@@ -63,6 +63,18 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n - **How to sign up**: Create an event-specific account via \u201cOneCebby\u201d to stay updated, find teams, and track participation.\n - **Notes**: Full details on the [Cebu Community blog here](https://hacktoberfest.jscebu.org)\n \n+#### Chimoney  \n+\n+- **Swag**: Digital badges & monetary incentives for selected contributions\n+- **Requirements**:  \n+    - Explore **open issues** in the [Chimoney Community Projects](https://github.com/Chimoney/chimoney-community-projects/issues) repository or **propose your own idea**.  \n+    - **Fork the repository**, create a **new branch**, make your changes, and **open a pull request**.  \n+    - Follow the **folder structure:** contributions go into the `submissions/` directory, with subfolders for SDKs, articles, etc.  \n+    - Review Chimoney\u2019s [contribution guidelines](https://github.com/Chimoney/chimoney-community-projects/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md) for details and examples.  \n+- **How to sign up**: No known signup link. \n+- **Issues**: [Chimoney Community Projects \u2013 GitHub Issues](https://github.com/Chimoney/chimoney-community-projects/issues)  \n+- **Notes**: Join the [Chimoney Discord](https://discord.com/invite/TsyKnzT4qV) for project updates, contribution guidance, and reward details, and [read their Hacktoberfest blog post here](https://chimoney.io/blogs/hacktoberfest-2025-build-contribute-and-learn-with-chimoney/).\n+\n #### Cloudinary\n \n - **Swag**: The first 30 participants to submit a valid pull request to one of the Cloudinary SDK repos (see below) are rewarded with:\n@@ -77,7 +89,7 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n - **How to sign up**: Once your contribution is accepted and merged, they'll provide you with an address form.\n - **Notes**: Full details on the [Cloudinary blog here](https://cloudinary.com/blog/hacktoberfest-2025)\n \n-#### **CopilotKit**\n+#### CopilotKit\n \n - **Swag**: CopilotKit swag\n - **Requirements**:\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Add  Chimoney to the Hacktoberfest Swag List for 2025\nA good first issue for people celebrating Hacktoberfest!\n\n[Chimoney](https://chimoney.io/blogs/hacktoberfest-2025-build-contribute-and-learn-with-chimoney/), is joining in on the Hacktoberfest fun. Contribute to Chimoney projects to earn rewards, badges and monetary incentives.\n\nPlease add them to the 2025 list following the formatting in the [CONTRIBUTING.md file.](https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/blob/master/docs/contributing.md)\n\nYou will need to locate the type of swag being offered, their requirements, and a link to their signup form (or some info on how they are tracking contributors).\n\nBe sure to register for Hacktoberfest first by [clicking here.](https://hacktoberfest.com/)\n\n _Issues are not assigned here. The first valid PR gets merged. So feel free to open a new PR._\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/3138859ea602fc182864e7f021e438574c5c89f5", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/1055ea0bce129b0624b53a5c7bd5a3f3e7b312cb"], "created_at": "2025-10-07T13:37:31Z"}
{"repo": "crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list", "pull_number": 1054, "instance_id": "crweiner__hacktoberfest-swag-list-1054", "issue_numbers": [1053], "base_commit": "94a63800fc1b1bd37e11e0037987bcc279512545", "patch": "diff --git a/docs/list.md b/docs/list.md\nindex 4dc7c7ca..c5ee4e58 100644\n--- a/docs/list.md\n+++ b/docs/list.md\n@@ -176,6 +176,17 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n - **Issues**: [This link shows the included repos and issues](https://github.com/search?q=topic%3Ahacktoberfest+org%3Ainterledger+fork%3Atrue+repo%3Awicg%2Fwebmonetization&type=repositories).\n - **Notes**: See their [Hacktoberfest page here](https://interledger.org/hacktoberfest).\n \n+#### iTop\n+\n+- **Swag**: iTop Hacktoberfest stickers, exclusive iTop insulated bottle, and discounts on iTop extensions.\n+- **Requirements**:\n+    - 1 PR: iTop Hacktoberfest stickers\n+    - 3 PRs: iTop insulated bottle\n+    - 6+ PRs: voucher for a free iTop extension (up to 75\u20ac value) and a 50% discount on additional extensions\n+- **How to sign up**: No known signup link.\n+- **Issues**: Check out the repositories tagged for Hacktoberfest contributions on [iTop\u2019s GitHub](https://github.com/Combodo).\n+- **Notes**: Read the [announcement](https://combodo.com/ecosystem/join-us-for-hacktoberfest/) for more details.\n+\n ### L\n \n #### Lamatic\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Add iTop to the Hacktoberfest Swag List for 2025\nA good first issue for people celebrating Hacktoberfest!\n\n[iTop](https://combodo.com/ecosystem/join-us-for-hacktoberfest/), is joining in on the Hacktoberfest fun. Contribute to one of 30 iTop or Combodo repositories to win bottles, stickers, vouchers etc\n\nPlease add them to the 2025 list following the formatting in the [CONTRIBUTING.md file.](https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/blob/master/docs/contributing.md)\n\nYou will need to locate the type of swag being offered, their requirements, and a link to their signup form (or some info on how they are tracking contributors).\n\nBe sure to register for Hacktoberfest first by [clicking here.](https://hacktoberfest.com/)\n\n_Issues are not assigned here. The first valid PR gets merged. So feel free to open a new PR._\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/2f6bbd347e009c42785f0500ba69233fc96062fe", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/cb14aea7bbe6945cfdf8630aa2986a3a8e96b004", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/e431feb45766972dfb779fc9d56f0ab03615336d", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/bc1352bc8664a02c297e4141e560bc165221e547"], "created_at": "2025-10-08T05:20:59Z"}
{"repo": "crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list", "pull_number": 1059, "instance_id": "crweiner__hacktoberfest-swag-list-1059", "issue_numbers": [1058], "base_commit": "f8c4ec0a38239e5631c34397009675bb195e8dab", "patch": "diff --git a/docs/list.md b/docs/list.md\nindex a4178ed6..f7c54b63 100644\n--- a/docs/list.md\n+++ b/docs/list.md\n@@ -346,6 +346,20 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n - **Issues**: [Open issues on Twenty GitHub](https://github.com/twentyhq/twenty/issues?q=is%3Aissue+label%3Ahacktoberfest).\n - **Notes**: Full event details and project ideas are available in the [official Hacktoberfest 2025 Notion page](https://twentycrm.notion.site/Hacktoberfest-27711d8417038037a149d4638a9cc510).\n \n+### W\n+\n+#### WSO2\n+\n+- **Swag**: Amazon Vouchers, WSO2 Goodies,Free vouchers for WSO2 Practitioner and Developer certifications, $1000 USD Worth credits for WSO2 cloud products.\n+- **Requirements**:\n+    - Select an issue from the Hacktoberfest project board below.\n+    - Leave a comment on the issue once you start working on it.\n+    - Submit a PR and address any review comments, if needed, and get your PR merged.\n+    - After your PR is merged, fill out the form below.\n+- **How to sign up**: Fill out [this form](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1tn3F1k3mERAXOCNNFOzX9i6rSSwbVcGkgkGL93Bgo5s/viewform?edit_requested=true) once the PR is merged.\n+- **Issues**: [See the open issues on WSO2 GitHub project board here](https://github.com/orgs/wso2/projects/134/).\n+- **Notes**: For more information please refer to [official WSO2 blog](https://wso2.com/hacktoberfest/).\n+\n ---\n \n *Disclaimer*: This website is a fan and community made creation. It is not affiliated with [Hacktoberfest](https://hacktoberfest.com/) or any company offering swag.\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Add WSO2 Swag opportunity\nSwags:  \n\n<img width=\"928\" height=\"326\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/1bfd8ec4-e787-463e-8aa8-4ef36adf0f0a\" />\n\nRequirement:\nRefer to the Hacktoberfest project board and select an issue to work on once it is completed fill this [form](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1tn3F1k3mERAXOCNNFOzX9i6rSSwbVcGkgkGL93Bgo5s/viewform?edit_requested=true)\n\nFor additional information please read this [blog](https://wso2.com/hacktoberfest/)\n", "hints_text": "I would like to work on this issue\n\n\n", "all_hints_text": "I would like to work on this issue\n\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/c4f2b0e4ac5f2cc93e5bddd0b7beb37d83c32a09", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/b6bfaec6227086e293509bc2336c45829d638aba"], "created_at": "2025-10-15T20:52:52Z"}
{"repo": "crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list", "pull_number": 1064, "instance_id": "crweiner__hacktoberfest-swag-list-1064", "issue_numbers": [1061], "base_commit": "12d872c5845e3d2500e585ae2451b682369de406", "patch": "diff --git a/docs/list.md b/docs/list.md\nindex dbc95158..7f5d8894 100644\n--- a/docs/list.md\n+++ b/docs/list.md\n@@ -361,6 +361,20 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n \n ### W\n \n+#### WeMakeDevs\n+\n+- **Swag**: Apple MacBook, Apple iPad, Interview opportunities at Kestra for the top contributors\n+- **Requirements**:\n+    - Register for the challenge and join the [Kestra Slack community](https://kestra-io.slack.com/join/shared_invite/zt-2u3tfbhch-BSZmQKJtgbMvprneNEL_HQ#/shared-invite/email).\n+    - Start contributing to open issues in [Kestra's repository](https://github.com/kestra-io/kestra/issues).\n+    - Follow the contribution guidelines: comment on the issue before starting, get it assigned, then submit a PR.\n+    - Write a short blog post about your experience and submit it during the final week to be eligible for prizes.\n+- **How to sign up**: Fill out [this form](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeNz4uTgojCQWlLsyTgOFHJ8I90gLmDIH-SBIMILfMAHMsJeQ/viewform).\n+- **Issues**: Contribute to real-world issues in [Kestra's GitHub repository](https://github.com/kestra-io/kestra/issues).\n+- **Notes**:\n+    - Event runs from 14 Oct \u2013 3 Nov.\n+    - Full event details at [WeMakeDevs Open Source Fest page](https://www.wemakedevs.org/hackathons/opensourcefest25).\n+\n #### WSO2\n \n - **Swag**: Amazon Vouchers, WSO2 Goodies,Free vouchers for WSO2 Practitioner and Developer certifications, $1000 USD Worth credits for WSO2 cloud products.\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Add WeMakeDevs to Hacktoberfest Swag List 2025\nWeMakeDevs's Open Source Fest from 13th October 2025 - 3rd Nov 2025 has prizes and employment opportunities. \nhttps://www.wemakedevs.org/hackathons/opensourcefest25\n\n@crweiner Can we add this to the list?\nThey don't exclusively give swag for the hacktoberfest event, but Kestra is a loud advocate of hacktoberfest since the beginning and this hackathon coincides with the hacktoberfest event and their repos are participating in `hacktoberfest`. \n\n_This issue is open for anyone to work on._ \nPlease read the [contributing guidelines](https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/blob/master/docs/contributing.md), and check any open PRs related to this issue before contributing. \n\nThank you\n\n\n", "hints_text": "@vimode i was thinking about adding this one but just show your issue. can i work on this one if it is allowed ?\n\n\n", "all_hints_text": "@vimode i was thinking about adding this one but just show your issue. can i work on this one if it is allowed ?\n\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/fa6ab251365585bee2117686b40b07e71a914f3e", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/903ed8edf806543f4b1bf188862953d0ce473d51"], "created_at": "2025-10-17T07:53:03Z"}
{"repo": "crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list", "pull_number": 1063, "instance_id": "crweiner__hacktoberfest-swag-list-1063", "issue_numbers": [1062], "base_commit": "12d872c5845e3d2500e585ae2451b682369de406", "patch": "diff --git a/docs/list.md b/docs/list.md\nindex dbc95158..8d679367 100644\n--- a/docs/list.md\n+++ b/docs/list.md\n@@ -245,6 +245,14 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n - **How to sign up**: No known signup link.\n - **Notes**: Find out more details [in their Hacktoberfest repo](https://github.com/LambdaTest/lambdatest-hacktoberfest-2025).\n \n+#### Layer5\n+\n+- **Swag**: Digital Badge\n+- **Requirements**: Participants must submit contributions during HacktoberFest (October) via PRs to Layer5 projects.\n+- **How to sign up**: No known signup link.\n+- **Issues**: [Layer 5 Hacktoberfest Issues](https://github.com/issues?q=is%3Aopen+is%3Aissue+archived%3Afalse+%28org%3Alayer5io+OR+org%3Ameshery+OR+org%3Aservice-mesh-performance+OR+org%3Aservice-mesh-patterns+OR+org%3Alayer5labs+OR+org%3Ameshery-extensions%29+label%3Ahacktoberfest)\n+- **Notes**: Check out the [blog post](https://layer5.io/programs/hacktoberfest) for more details.\n+\n #### LocalStack\n \n - **Swag**: Unknown\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Add Layer5 Swag\n**Swag :** Digital Badge\n\n<img width=\"178\" height=\"258\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/04787c96-67da-428d-b157-f27f0e9832b3\" />\n\n**Requirement:**  contributing to Layer5 projects during this Hacktoberfest.\n\nFor More Information read [blog](https://layer5.io/programs/hacktoberfest)\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/b4f3faa1d7d93aa1d6ea94aa02f1b09bd4769c48", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/eedc1727295024c359a45a78e2aefb8dc008b17f", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/3bc624817a622d40bbd92eb466422140153eeec5"], "created_at": "2025-10-16T13:35:37Z"}
{"repo": "crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list", "pull_number": 1066, "instance_id": "crweiner__hacktoberfest-swag-list-1066", "issue_numbers": [1065], "base_commit": "12d872c5845e3d2500e585ae2451b682369de406", "patch": "diff --git a/docs/list.md b/docs/list.md\nindex dbc95158..8ac40ed3 100644\n--- a/docs/list.md\n+++ b/docs/list.md\n@@ -336,6 +336,18 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n \n ### S\n \n+#### Serplux\n+\n+- **Swag**: T Shirt\n+- **Requirements**:\n+    - Submit at least 2 valid PRs that are merged.\n+    - Developers can contribute through improving code, solving bugs, writing test cases and improving code quality.\n+    - Designers and Marketers can contribute through creating social post banners, logos, or improving the presentation of the Serplux website pages and blog posts.\n+    - Writers and Content creators can write tech blogs, walkthrough tech videos or how to guides.\n+- **How to sign up**: Fill out this [form](https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSf9UW15IOT9hPYehUjqkgOUXerHeYnrm5Cova_PwGosryyvjg/viewform) your 2 PRs are merged.\n+- **Issues**: [See example Issues on the Serplux Blog Repository](https://github.com/Serplux/blog/issues)\n+- **Notes**: Read their [full Hacktoberfest blog post here](https://blog.serplux.com/hacktoberfest-2025/)\n+\n #### Service Now\n \n - **Swag**: ServiceNow merch store codes, and a Community Badge\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Add Serplux Swag opportunity\n**Swags:** Serplux Hacktoberfest 2025 T-shirts\n\n**Requirement:** Submit at least 2 valid PRs that get merged during Hacktoberfest 2025. Be among first 500 qualified contributors.\n\nFor more Information read the [blog](https://blog.serplux.com/hacktoberfest-2025/) \n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/775fc3e01f4361d32ed07b88c5825b1e8ea8d635", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/01dd7343e91f295e0d94ec7f8c00ca8fea4c4bc5", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/fc668c0dbdebbae64734fd336dce4d52daa5117d", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/abdb48ea2d38a7df56fdeb6eb11874acd16f4773"], "created_at": "2025-10-17T11:37:01Z"}
{"repo": "crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list", "pull_number": 1073, "instance_id": "crweiner__hacktoberfest-swag-list-1073", "issue_numbers": [1072], "base_commit": "12d872c5845e3d2500e585ae2451b682369de406", "patch": "diff --git a/docs/list.md b/docs/list.md\nindex dbc95158..5ffeed7b 100644\n--- a/docs/list.md\n+++ b/docs/list.md\n@@ -259,6 +259,13 @@ Do you want to put your project in front of tens of thousands of developers duri\n \n ### M\n \n+#### Microsoft 365 & Power Platform Community\n+\n+- **Swag**: Digital Badges\n+- **Requirements**: Contribute to the [Microsoft 365 Repo](https://github.com/microsoft/Microsoft365DSC) and/or [Power Platform Community](https://community.powerplatform.com/) and earn the digital badges.\n+- **How to sign up**: Fill out this [form](https://aka.us11.list-manage.com/subscribe?u=b3df03dd2b64a3bc8a2a200e8&id=4a558f9e2b) when your contributions are merged.\n+- **Notes**: [Check out this X Post for more details](https://x.com/DavidWarnerII/status/1975372755509125315).\n+\n #### **MindsDB**\n \n - **Swag**: Github Sponsorship, MindsDB T-shirt, MacBook Pro\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Add Microsoft 365 & Power Platform Community Swags\nIts chance to learn and earn a badge.\n\n**Swags:** Digital Badges\n\n<img width=\"1600\" height=\"900\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/d109043d-ce3b-4c25-a2d7-c599d9645e55\" />\n\n**Requirement:**  Contribute to Microsoft 365 repo and Power platform community.\n\nFor additional Information read [X post](https://x.com/DavidWarnerII/status/1975372755509125315)\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/a2f6fae843781eb6f4dd1b7e964446205141d114", "https://github.com/crweiner/hacktoberfest-swag-list/commit/27d85df6c193ebe6b9d17062f7ea0b06512a26af"], "created_at": "2025-10-18T08:10:38Z"}
